data.description: Unique Double Lot Victorian Residence in Hallam Borough! .67 Acres - Detached Garage - Carriage House and patio. Lot meets basic dimensional requirements for subdivision. Feasibility study needed. This grand Victorian home greets you with a spacious front porch. Original double doors give way to a living room with high ceilings adorned with beautifully detailed woodwork and a windowed library that includes a built in book case with sliding ladder. The formal dining room includes a wood stove flue and pressed metal ceiling tiles. The country kitchen has stainless steel appliances, granite countertops and connects to a breakfast nook. The main level bath includes historic stained glass detail and pedestal sink. The generous primary ensuite boasts ample closet space, updated tile shower with glass door, and heated flooring. The primary is paired on the second level with 2 large bedrooms, a second full bath, and a laundry room. From the laundry one can access the attic bonus room perfect for storage, children's play room, or additional living space. Exit the main level from the back onto a covered back porch with included gas flat top grills and spa. This property includes two conjoined outbuildings, both with electricity: a deep one car garage and work space, and a carriage house with a concrete patio that is finished on the main level into a bedroom. The property also includes several mature fruit trees - cherry, pear, and apple. This is a can't miss opportunity to own a piece of history on a one of a kind lot in the borough.
